element.name: Sidetracked-Leixlip Confey by Kili or Bust, Traditional Cache (1.5/1.5)
element.long-description:
Sidetracked-Leixlip Confey
The cache is a small round metal magnetic container. It is intended as an easy find. There is no need to enter the station proper or access the platform at all.
Small train station on the border of counties Dublin and Kildare.
Leixlip Confey is a railway station serving Leixlip, County Kildare, Ireland, one of two railway stations serving the area, the other being Leixlip Louisa Bridge. Both stations lie on the Dublin to Longford commuter route.

2010-03-18T19:00:00Z : Didn't find it by sonofbelial
Interesting - didn't find it as advertised while gingerly routing around the condom wrappers etc. BUT I did find a couple of rucksacks hidden which contained some kids' stash of fireworks... These I removed so if you see a couple of ransacked backpacks down there - that's what that was from. No sign of any metal container though [?]
